ESFM v0.5 PSA

Note: This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text before using in public. Some things (like capitalisation of “him” referring to Jesus or “father” referring to God) in the RV haven’t been decided yet so we’re still testing both ways.

Note: The Readers’ Version on the left is a translation into contemporary English aimed at the person on the street who hasn’t necessarily been brought up with exposure to Biblical jargon and/or King James English. It’s designed to be used alongside the Literal Version on the right which gives the English reader a window into what’s actually written in the original languages. (See the introduction for more details—we recommend that you read the introduction first if you’re wanting to fully understand the Literal Version.) By comparing the left and right columns, you should be able to easily get the message of the text, while at the same time keeping an eye on what it was actually translated from.

Psalms

It is our prayer that the Open English Translation of the Bible will give you clear understanding of the messages written by the inspired Biblical writers.

Introduction

The Psalm, sabeka seini immanlimud me ulahingen, me duma pad man‑e me ulahingen, me balak, and me praying. Inggamit sika te keet-etawan te Israel te pegsimba ran. Nataman, intimul ran e seini diye te me Kasulatan dan.

Masulug klasi te seini epad te egmalintutuu te God: due me ulahingen te pegsaye and pegsimba te God, due me praying te egpabulig, and te kaluwasan, pegbuyu te pasaylu, ulahingen te egpasalamat te pegpanalangin te God, and me peghangyu egdusaan ka me kuntere dan. The seini me praying neelin para te senge-person and para te intiru inged; ka duma, migpakita te peg-ealig te person, ka duma, migpanengneng te me keilangan and peggeyinawa te langun keet-etawan te God.

Inggamit of Jesus ka me ulahingen, inlagkes isulat te me talagsulat te Iyam Panugtulen, and intumpisan e seini baseen te pegsimba te Simbaan te Migmalintutuu puun te pegbunsud.

Main components of this “book”

The sabeka gatus and lalimma pulu (150) me ulahingen, imbaad te lalimma baad and ke baseen naa:

Psa. (1–41)

Psalm (42–72)

Psalm (73–89)

Psalm (90–106)

Psalm (107–150)

Te seini baseen, due sabeka gatus and lalimma pulu (150) me ulahingen and me praying inggamit te me Hebrews te pegsimba ran. Eggamiten dan sika te pegsimba ran diye te kasuluhan, and diye te eglunsud-lunsud de pegsimba. The duma kayi, inggamit dan te timpu pad of Hari Dabid, kema ke sikandin iya ka talagsulat kayi. Ne ka duma, and buwad nasulat napenge e ka peghari of Dabid. Ne ka sika me ulahingen and praying, impurtanti pad kuntee eggamiten te pegsimba te me Hebrews me migmalintutuu. The Psalm, migpataha ke nekey ka eggeramen te person, iling te: kaaldek egpangkus te kahale, kabelu egpangkus te pegsalig and pegkalange egpangkus te peg-iman-iman.

See also the FAQs and the Glossary.

(2 Sam. 22:1-51)

60:1 The pegpangananey te God

The ulahingen of Dabid para te pegpanulu, para te pangulu te mangngulahing. Insulat din seini te migpakiggira sikandin te me matig-Aram-Naharaim and te me matig-Aram-Suba, and te nakalibed e si Huwab and nekeyimatey te 12,000 me matig-Idum diye te bangalug egngaranan te Asin. Eg-ulahingen seini iling te peg-ulahing te “Liryu te Pangguhuren.”
